<p><i><b>The Story of My Experiments with Truth</b></i> (<a href="/wiki/Gujarati_language" title="Gujarati language">Gujarātī</a> "સત્યના પ્રયોગો અથવા આત્મકથા" <a href="/w/index.php?title=English_transliteration&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="English transliteration (page does not exist)">transliterated</a>: Satyanā Prayogo athvā Ātmakathā) is the <a href="/wiki/Autobiography" title="Autobiography">autobiography</a> of <a href="/wiki/Mohandas_Karamchand_Gandhi" title="Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi">Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi</a>, covering his life from early childhood through to 1920. It was initiated at the insistence of <i>Swami Anand</i> and other close co-workers of Gandhi, for him to explain the background of his public campaigns. In <a href="/wiki/1999" title="1999">1999</a>, the book was designated as one of the <i>"100 Most Important Spiritual Books of the 20th Century"</i> by <a href="/wiki/HarperCollins" title="HarperCollins">HarperCollins</a> publishers.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
